ce:section.ce:para:
The percentage of the live cells, early apoptotic, and late apoptotic/necrotic stages were evaluated using a modified method of annexin V-FITC and PI staining by flow cytometry method (Ma et al., 2018). The percentage of live cells decreased from 98.22% (control cells) to 80.18% and 34.62% for the cells treated with 3 to 6 mg mL−1 
                        Salmo salar L. CQDs, respectively (Fig. 5
                        ). No obvious change indicated that NRK cells treated with Salmo salar L. CQDs were in early apoptosis stage. There was an increase of 8.34% and 10.30% in the proportion of cells in late apoptosis stage and necrosis after treatment with 3 and 6 mg mL−1 of Salmo salar L. CQDs, respectively. A CQD concentration-dependent increase in cells apoptosis, increasing with the CQD concentration, suggests differential sensitivity to Salmo salar L. CQDs concentrations. In addition, the proportion of apoptotic and necrotic cells in the cells treated with CQDs increased from 23.23 to 93.3% with the increase of the CQD concentration from 3 to 6 mg/mL. Accordingly, the proportion of apoptotic and necrosis cells showed that the glucose CDs are more toxic than the Salmo salar L. CQDs.
